Important nutrition update:
The district‚Äôs weekday meal distribution will continue through Aug. 10 at five locations. The free, to-go meal distribution will continue to take place 11 a.m. to noon Monday through Friday. Included in the distribution are three meals per day as well as four additional meals on Friday to cover the weekend.
Effective Thursday, June 4, the five distribution locations for summer will be:
Central Elementary, 122 W. Fourth Ave.
Farr Avenue Elementary, 933 Farr Ave.
Felicita Elementary, 737 W. 13th Ave.
Glen View Elementary, 2201 E. Mission Ave.
Oak Hill Elementary, 1820 Oak Hill Drive

What an exciting day today at Farr Avenue Elementary School - EUSD: Our Farr Falcons enjoyed a very special visit from 10News ‚Äì ABC San Diego KGTV and the Scripps Howard Foundation, which brought more than 1,000 new books for our young readers ‚Äì all donated by 10News employees. Wow!
We are so grateful to have been chosen as a partner for the news station and foundation's "If You Give a Child a Book" campaign.
Tune in to 10News ‚Äì ABC San Diego KGTV at 6 p.m. tonight for more on the National Reading Day event, followed by a special report on literacy at 7:30 p.m.
Additional thanks to our friends at San Diego County Office of Education as well as Scholastic Book Fairs Warehouse - San Diego Branch for their support!

Power shutoff update:
Conway Elementary School will resume normal operations on Thursday, Oct. 31, following a daylong closure Wednesday as a result of a public safety power shutoff alert by San Diego Gas & Electric.
On Thursday, all Conway Elementary students should report to school according to the usual Thursday bell schedule. In addition, all other EUSD schools and the District Office will be open Thursday.
The public safety power shutoff warning was prompted by a forecast of adverse weather conditions. The safety and security of students and employees are of the utmost importance to EUSD.

post_text: Important information for our Conway community
shared_text:
Escondido Union School District
October 29, 2019 at 10:27 PM ¬∑

Conway Elementary School will be closed to students on Wednesday, Oct. 30, as a result of a public safety power shutoff activated by San Diego Gas & Electric.

The public safety power shutoff, prompted by a forecast of adverse weather conditions, is expected to be activated by 4 a.m. Wednesday. The safety and security of students and employees are of the utmost importance to EUSD.

Conway Elementary staff members should report to school at their usual time. A generator will provide limited power to select areas of campus.

No additional EUSD schools are affected at this time. All other EUSD schools and the District Office will remain open Wednesday.

Conway Elementary staff members should report to school at their usual time. A generator will provide limited power to select areas of campus.

No additional EUSD schools are affected at this time. All other EUSD schools and the District Office will remain open Wednesday.

post_text:
In EUSD, we treasure our community partners, who provide invaluable opportunities and support. We are fortunate to have A Step Beyond among those partners. This Saturday, Oct. 5, the Escondido nonprofit is hosting its annual auditions for new students.
A Step Beyond serves children in our community through its multi-year program, which provides dance education, academic programs, and family services to low-income families. Students accepted into the program receive free dance classes, and so much more, including free tutoring, academic support, and college-prep workshops; family workshops; and counseling services.
Audition details:
Oct. 5 at the California Center for the Arts, Escondido
8:30 a.m., ages 8 to 10
11 a.m., ages 10 to 14
Students must be accompanied by a legal guardian.

This #ThrowbackThursday, we're taking a trip to Escondido Village Mall ‚Äì the first enclosed mall in Southern California. The mall was ahead of its time in providing shoppers with relief from the heat.
The district, too, has been ahead of its time, showcasing technology, science, music, and more at its EUSD Education Fair held at Escondido Village Mall. It was May 1983.
Today, EUSD has the opportunity to highlight innovation daily here on social media, as well as with annual events like the smART Festival, Escondido Youth Media Festival, and State of the District event!
#ChooseEUSD #ThrowbackThursday #aheadofitstime #EUSDinnovation #EUSDcommunity

Do you have an EUSD photo or yearbook you would like to share with us for a future #ThrowbackThursday? Email us at communications@eusd.org.

Here at the district office, we have a dedicated social committee that encourages colleagues to get to know one another, whether it's bonding during an ice cream social or giving back to the community with a donation drive.
To kick of this school year, the social committee launched a Backpack Drive, with a goal of collecting 100 new backpacks, along with school supplies, for students in need in our community. Thanks to generous employees and community members, the team is just a few backpacks away from meeting its goal. And special thanks go out to Escondido Smile Center for its donation of more than 40 backpacks!

#giveback #caringcommunity #dogood #ChooseEUSD #backpackdrive

June 13, 2019 at 9:05 AM ¬∑

School is out, but that doesn't mean the learning and teaching has stopped! This week, our expanded learning team has been busy working with teachers and community partners preparing for three different summer programs for our students.

Summer Scholars Academy Elementary Intervention and Enrichment includes math instruction, PE, and enrichment activities from our partners at Palomar Family YMCA, San Diego Children's Discovery Museum, and Treobytes.

The Elementary School GATE Summer Institute: Camp Invention uses the "Supercharged" STEAM curriculum from the National Inventors Hall of Fame.

The Middle School GATE Summer Institute: Camp Exploration features all-day, off-site field work with our partners from The Nature Collaborative.

In addition, EUSD is offering Open Library at Conway Elementary! Stay tuned for more as our summer learning kicks off next week.

#innovate #education #ChooseEUSD #learningneverstops #nosummerslide

The first year of our Allegro Strings Program ‚Äì a music enrichment opportunity in partnership with San Diego Civic Youth Orchestra with support of philanthropists Jean and Bob Will ‚Äì concluded with a beautiful concert in front of a packed house Wednesday evening. Our budding violinists and cellists performed for proud family members, teachers, and community members.
EUSD is proud to offer this musical experience to 130 3rd-, 4th-, and 5th-graders, with representation from nearly every district elementary school.
From the outstanding renditions of "Hot Cross Buns," Twinkle Variations "Ode to Joy," and more, one would never know that these young musicians started learning their instruments only months ago.

Escondido Union School District added 16 new photos ‚Äî with San Diego Oasis at North Broadway Elementary School.
April 26, 2019 at 7:27 PM ¬∑ Escondido, CA ¬∑

Who doesn‚Äôt love to pick out a new book? Thanks to senior volunteers from San Diego Oasis, North Broadway 1st-, 2nd-, and 3rd-graders were invited to pick out three books during a book giveaway Friday morning. Hundreds of books went home with eager young readers, many of whom sought out something new, while others had their sights set on books about sports, science, Star Wars, and superheroes.

This is the third year that Oasis has presented a book giveaway to North Broadway students, and in just a couple of weeks the volunteers will visit Rock Springs to do the same. Oasis volunteers said they like to plan the book giveaway days as close to summer break as possible, to give children a few extra books of their choosing to take home for summer.

One of San Diego Oasis' many programs is its intergenerational tutoring service, which pairs an older adult one-on-one with a student who needs some extra help with reading. Some 85 tutors are assisting 158 students at 11 EUSD schools every week! The adult stays paired with the same student throughout the school year.

post_text: Four Escondido Union High School District campuses hosted nearly 800 8th-graders from EUSD‚Äôs Quantum Academy, Rincon Middle School, and Hidden Valley Middle School - EUSD today as part of the annual ‚ÄúJump Aboard‚Äù 8th-grade student tours program. Now in its sixth year, the high school district's "Jump Aboard" introduces students from Escondido Union School District, along with neighboring San Pasqual Union, to the exciting Career and Technical Education (CTE) programs, extracurricular activities, and other college-prep programs available on EUHSD campuses. More than 900 8th-graders from Bear Valley Middle School - EUSD, Mission Middle School, and Del Dios Academy of Arts and Sciences will jump aboard on Wednesday. We love our partnership with Escondido Union High School District, and we are full of gratitude for our awesome hosts from San Pasqual High School, Orange Glen High School, Escondido High School, and Del Lago Academy - Campus of Applied Science.

The holiday gained even more understanding and recognition with last year‚Äôs hit Disney film, ‚ÄúCoco.‚Äù And locally, our city‚Äôs own California Center for the Arts, Escondido, has hosted a huge D√≠a de los Muertos Festival for more than 22 years!
